The paper deals with modeling and understanding mobile networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computer networks (cs.NI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also proposes an algorithm for efficient computation, which is a topic that falls under the scope of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper applies the concept of temporal reachability graphs to synthetic and real-life datasets, which is a topic that falls under the scope of social and information networks (cs.SI).
